25303">Samir Shaidar`mai</a><br>Warlord of the MOFIA Variety<br>AKA The Odorous One</td><td><img src="http://casan_eq.homestead.com/Files/monkey.gif"></td></tr></table></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/urobaz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Robaz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 99<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/12/02 10:50:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2354.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> sounds fun</span><hr size=1> Basically I post here because I have longed to be part of history.  Now that I get up in levels the game is changing and becoming more fun and challenging.  <br><br>As an unguilded and frail cleric, I am not all wise but perhaps we could get some cooperation going to complete this quest.  It would be fun to be the first server to get the key.  It sounds from the post that this is uber time consuming and fairly detailed, I suggest perhaps some kind of multi-guild cooperation and sharing of information.<br><br>Not sure if it could be done but how about some of us get together and plan raids / share information to work toward the quest.  I have no idea just how hard this quest is, but I would guess that Vazaelle would not have a chance to be first unless there is cooperation.  It might be that the only way to do this would be the sharing of information amongst people in multiple guilds.  The problem I see is the trusting of secret information.  It is obvious that stuff is being held back because everyone is racing to do this quest.  <br><br>I would like to know what others think.  Could Vazaelle be first? If so what would it take?  Could a bunch of trustworthy people be able to do this regarldless of guild affiliation?   <br><br>A lone cleric is certainly of little use, but I offer whatever frail help my withered old body can give and pledge loyalty to any who would trust me to help in such a quest.  If there are already some people on Vaz working on this behind the scenes, I wish you the best of luck and hope you are the first to complete this quest.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   GO VAZ !!<br><br><br><br>Robaz<br>Vazaelle<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/ukatarinandolini.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Katarin Andolini</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Contributing Member</span><br>  Posts: 179<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/12/02 3:06:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2354.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.smilies-world.de/Smilies/Smilies_klein/Smilies_klein_1/booaa.gif height=40 width=40></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: sounds fun</span><hr size=1> Hmm, ok, theorizing a little.<br><br>Someone noticed &quot;a shimmering presence&quot; (invisible; a whisperling?) in Akheva awhile back in the area across from the Itraer Vius.  The following dialogue transpired (taken from the Safehouse):<br><br><!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> You say, 'Hail, A shimmering presence'<br><br>A shimmering presence 's voice invades your mind, drawing images of past present and future together into a perverse harmony. Some images you recognize as your own, but the others seem to be coming from the spirit's own [memories]. '<br><br>You say, 'what memories'<br><br>A shimmering presence begins to glow a bit brighter. Your mind is filled with visions of a great swirl of clouds and lightning. You can almost feel the wind of the storm creeping into the chinks in your armor. It looks as if the storm is creeping across the surface of Luclin. You see several figures standing at the entrance of a [great temple]. The storm seems to be bearing down on them. '<br><br>You say, 'what great temple'<br><br>A shimmering presence continues to flood your mind with images of the storm bearing down on the temple. Your view suddenly shifts. You're still looking at the storm, but it appears to be moving toward you this time. There is a creature beside you wearing a robe, holding a scepter in one of his...four arms! He is obviously the leader of the group, As he is wearing beautiful [ornate robes] compared to the rest of the four armed figures around you. '<br><br>You say, 'what ornate robes'<br><br>A shimmering presence glows brighter still as your vision turns to follow the robed figure up the stairs of the entrance to the temple. The figure raises his scepter toward the storm and begins to recite some unfamiliar words. A crackle of magical energy blazes across the sky seemingly in defiance of the raging storm. The energy quickly dissipates however, and the storm continues to bear down on the temple. The figure cries out in pain as the scepter in his hand breaks into several pieces and falls to the ground.' <br><hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br><br>Perhaps this vision is a hint of where the Spirit of Akelha`Ra can be found?<br><br>Was thinking he might be a triggered spawn on the steps of the temple, where the stone guardians and Rumblecrush are.  But OTOH, the person who found the Spirit at Safehouse sounds like a single guy exploring, and to be able to do that and be visable and not worry about repops on the temple steps would be kind of rough.<br><br>~Kat <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/ukatarinandolini.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Katarin Andolini</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Contributing Member</span><br>  Posts: 180<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/12/02 3:20:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2354.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.smilies-world.de/Smilies/Smilies_klein/Smilies_klein_1/booaa.gif height=40 width=40></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: sounds fun</span><hr size=1> BTW, sounds like the key quest for Vex Thal was revamped with April 9th's patch, which is what has brought this new info to light.<br><br>cf:  <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showMessage?topicID=4666.topic">pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showMessage?topicID=4666.topic</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br><br>So revisiting some quest mobs might be a good idea as well...<br><br>With regards to the quest pieces other than the container:<br><br>Have personally seen the glowing orb of luclinite drop off the Va'dyn, and Rhags 1 and 2.  Other people say they are basically dropping off of all SoL boss and miniboss mobs now.<br><br>The Luclin shards seem to be dropping more randomly.  (ie not always the same one from the same mob)  Have seen them a few times but my memory's kinda hazy.  I remember The Protector mob in Akheva dropping a shard fairly regularly, however...<br><br>~Kat <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showPrevMessage?topicID=2354.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showNextMessage?topicID=2354.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2354.topic&index=3><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/addReply.gif border=0 alt="